<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other baseball games: 
</P>
<P>
Valley 10, El Camino 9 -- Mike Caputi singled in Harold Ciccione with the 
winning run with two out in the ninth inning of the nonconference game at 
Valley, capping a dramatic Monarch comeback. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing, 9-1, Valley (12-1-1) scored six runs in the eighth and three in the 
ninth. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 5, Chapman 4 -- Senior right-hander Jay Anderson allowed two runs 
in 7 1/3 innings and freshman Chris Matkin pitched out of jams in the eighth 
and ninth innings as Cal Lutheran won its sixth in a row in a nonconference 
game at Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific 5, The Master's 1 -- First baseman Jeff Preston and pitcher Peter 
Wilson were both two for four for Master's in an NAIA District 3 loss at Azusa 
Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 7, Pierce 5 -- Pierce erased a four-run deficit to tie the score, 5-5, 
but Pasadena hit solo home runs in the seventh and eighth innings in a 
nonconference game at Pierce. Damon Lantz hit a solo home run for Pierce (4-5). 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 5-2, Chapman 0-1 -- Debbie Dickmann won both games as CSUN 
(10-6 overall, 2-0 in conference play) swept a California Collegiate Athletic 
Assn. doubleheader at Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 1, Rancho Santiago 0 (9) -- De Dow pitched her first no-hitter and 
fifth shutout of the season in the nonconference game at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
CS Bakersfield 4-10, Cal Lutheran 2-2 -- The defending NCAA Division II 
champion Roadrunners took advantage of nine Cal Lutheran errors in a 
nonconference doubleheader at Cal Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
UCLA d. Cal State Northridge, 19-17, 15-7, 16-14 -- Northridge trailed, 7-1, in 
the opening game, rallied, and then blew three game-point opportunities before 
falling in a Western Intercollegiate Volleyball Assn. match at UCLA. 
</P>
