<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
 STEROID SHIPMENTS SEIZED, MAN HELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Several shipments of steroids from South America valued at more than $500,000 
have been confiscated and an employee of an air courier company arrested in El 
Segundo in the largest such seizure ever in the Los Angeles area, authorities 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Lowell Coble, 49, of Venice was taken into custody Saturday by U.S. Customs 
agents and members of a multi-agency police investigative team, Customs Pacific 
Regional Commissioner Quintin Villaneuva said. 
</P>
<P>
Coble's arrest and the seizure of more than 130,000 doses of steroids came 
after a Customs inspector became suspicious of a package from Brazil, 
Villaneuva said. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. Atty. Robert Bonner said a criminal complaint was filed against Coble, 
charging him with possessing a large quantity of anabolic steroids for sale and 
with receiving steroids while knowing that they had been illegally imported 
from Brazil. 
</P>
</TEXT>
