<P>
METRO DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
 TRUCK HITS STOPPED MOTORIST, OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pickup truck careened out of control on Highway 30 in San Dimas Tuesday, 
plowing into a California Highway Patrol officer and a driver he had stopped 
for a traffic ticket, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The officer was knocked off a bridge, falling nearly 40 feet to the road below. 
He suffered two broken arms, a broken leg and head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The motorist he had stopped was crushed by the pickup and may lose both of his 
legs, Los Angeles County Fire Department spokeswoman Arden Beer said. 
</P>
<P>
The pickup's driver suffered minor injuries and the cause of the crash was 
under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
