<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPAN TO PARTICIPATE IN SEVILLE EXPOSITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Japanese government will have a high-tech pavilion at the 1992 World 
Exposition in Seville, a Cabinet minister said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Hiroshi Mitsuzuka, minister for international trade and industry, said the 
government will spend $48 million on the building. 
</P>
<P>
The Seville event will commemorate the 500th anniversary of Columbus' discovery 
of America in 1492. Spain will also host the Barcelona Olympics in 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
JAPAN -- TRADE; SPAIN -- CELEBRATIONS; FAIRS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA030189-0060 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 24873 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
