<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
ROBBERY-SLAYING SUSPECT IS ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspect in the slaying of a Diamond Bar woman was arrested Tuesday morning at 
a Costa Mesa motel, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Allen David Brooks, 42, is being held in connection with the shotgun murder of 
Belinda Brecke, 31, in a Diamond Bar check-cashing store on Dec. 15, 1988. The 
suspect fled with $10,000 to $15,000, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Costa Mesa Police Lt. Gary Webster alleged that Brooks held up two Orange 
County restaurants Monday and escaped with an undetermined amount of money. 
</P>
<P>
A Costa Mesa patrol officer spotted a Dodge van about 3 a.m. parked outside the 
motel. The vehicle fit the description of a getaway vehicle used in the 
robberies. Police set up a small SWAT team outside of the motel about 6:30 a.m. 
and Brooks surrendered 15 minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
Police think that Brooks is a transient who lived at the hotel. 
</P>
<P>
He remains in custody of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
</TEXT>
