<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
NEWPORT HARBOR'S CURCI SIGNS TO PLAY AT CAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Newport Harbor High School's Sienna Curci, one of the nation's top girls' 
volleyball players, has signed a national letter of intent to attend California 
next fall, said Charlie Brande, Orange County Volleyball Club coach. 
</P>
<P>
Curci, a 5-foot-5 setter, helped Newport Harbor to the 5-A championship in 
1987. She considered UCLA and Stanford but decided on Cal, where brother Mike, 
a former standout at Newport Harbor, plays for the men's volleyball team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
