<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Associated Press report published Sunday incompletely described the verdict 
in the court-martial of Marine 1st Lt. Allen Lawson. He was convicted of 
dereliction of duty, of appearing drunk and of disobeying an order. The charges 
stemmed from the death of Lance Cpl. Jason Rother, who had been left behind in 
the Mojave Desert during a training exercise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
